The most common scenario in which digital communication failure creates difficulties is when a student writes an email or message without clarity and the right tone. A student might send a message to the professor through WhatsApp without clarity and the right tone. The student might send a message such as “Send notes fast.” This kind of message might be interpreted as rude and impolite by the professor.
This kind of digital communication failure might have been avoided by ensuring the right communication etiquette. The right communication etiquette would have ensured the student sent a message with the right context, such as greeting the professor, expressing the request in the right way, and thanking the professor. In digital communication, the right platform also plays a crucial role.
